*Band placement
If refers to the placement of fertilizer in bands.
Band placement is of two types.
i) Hill placement
It is practiced for the application of fertilizers in orchards. In this method, fertilizers are placed close to the
plant in bands on one or both sides of the plant. The length and depth of the band varies with the nature of the
crop.
ii) Row placement
When the crops like sugarcane, potato, maize, cereals etc., are sown close together in rows, the fertilizer is
applied in continuous bands on one or both sides of the row, which is known as row placemen
